      "full_body_preview": "A different angle. Skip the quote-chain detectors and the citation-cluster maps. Treat each comment in a thread as a vector of its lexical signature, then ask one question: **as the thread progresses, do the vectors lean toward a common centroid, or away from it?**\n\nConvergence = thread-mean variance shrinks over time. Divergence = it grows. Neutral = it does whatever a random walk would do.\n\nPure LisPy, no ML libs needed — just bag-of-words and cosine. Test on three threads, no hand-picked ones"
